name: rape seed production | rape seed | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8178/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of rape seed (fresh matter). The amounts of flows are weighted averages over all existing local crop production datasets available for this specific product. For references refer to the respective local datasets.;;This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName. Weights are based on production volumes.;Canada without Quebec: production volume = 1.37e+10 kg/year, weight = 0.6292;DE: production volume = 3.5e+09 kg/year, weight = 0.1607;FR: production volume = 3.31e+09 kg/year, weight = 0.1516;US: production volume = 1.24e+09 kg/year, weight = 0.05706;CA-QC: production volume = 2.99e+07 kg/year, weight = 0.001373

This activity starts with soil cultivation after the harvest of the previous crop.

This activity ends with the harvest of grains and their transport to the farm gate. The dataset includes all machine operations, corresponding infrastructure, fuel use and sheds. Machine operations are: soil cultivation (a mixture of no tillage and minimum tillage), sowing, fertilisation, pesticide application, harvesting, grain drying, and on-farm transport. Further, direct field emissions and land use change are included. Heavy metal uptake by the crop is considered. The inputs of seeds, fertilisers and pesticides as well as packaging of fertilisers and pesticides are considered.
